ZH: 我们今天晚上吃饭的时候，再算账吧。
EN: Let's settle the bill when we have dinner tonight.

ZH: 我们不要给谁添麻烦了，这次算账我来吧。
EN: Let me take care of the bill this time so we don't inconvenience anyone.

ZH: 你不要一直算账了，我们大家都知道你的诚实了。
EN: You don't have to keep settling the bill, we all know you're honest.

ZH: 我们分摊费用吧，这样每个人都会觉得公平。
EN: Let's split the costs so everyone feels it's fair.

ZH: 他们总是为谁该付账而争吵不休。
EN: They always argue about who should pay the bill.

ZH: 昨天晚上我们出去吃饭，最后还是她算了账。
EN: We went out for dinner last night and she ended up settling the bill.

ZH: 请你今晚出去玩一次，算我请你吧。
EN: Let me take you out tonight, my treat.

ZH: 这次出去吃饭，我来算账吧。
EN: Let me pay the bill for this meal.

ZH: 我只是希望我们都能独立支付自己的开支。
EN: I just hope we can all pay our own expenses independently.

ZH: 你为什么总要替他们算账呢？
EN: Why do you always settle the bill for them?

ZH: 这次我们的费用可以平摊，不必担心。
EN: This time we can split the costs, no need to worry.

ZH: 明天请你在我家吃饭，别忘了我算账。
EN: Don't forget I'll be the one paying the bill when you come to my house for dinner tomorrow.

ZH: 他们总是希望别人来算账，可是从不心疼人家钱包。
EN: They always expect others to pay the bill, but never feel sorry for their wallets.

ZH: 无论如何，我们最后都应该公平地分摊费用。
EN: In any case, we should all split the costs fairly in the end.

ZH: 他们真不懂得赚钱的不易，总是让别人算账。
EN: They really don't understand how hard it is to make money, always letting others settle the bill.

ZH: 我们出去旅行时，谁来算账都无所谓，只要大家开心就好。
EN: When we go on a trip, it doesn't matter who pays the bill as long as everyone is happy.

ZH: 下次去超市，我会带足够的钱来算账。
EN: I'll bring enough money to pay the bill next time we go to the supermarket.

ZH: 无论多少钱，我都会来算账。
EN: No matter how much it is, I'll pay the bill.

ZH: 在这种情况下，我们应该公平的分摊费用。
EN: In this situation, we should split the costs fairly.

ZH: 每次出去吃饭前，我们都会商量好谁来算账。
EN: Before we go out for dinner each time, we always decide who will settle the bill.
